		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> PA Open - 5/18/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.96)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=577'>Kimberly "Arwen Even*" Caton</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=577&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 20, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Okay, so I somehow managed to win the PA territorials.  This is my story...<br />
<br />
Was out until 2am the night before.  Left at 8:30 in a downpour, met up with John Lolli, Mike Dalton, Chris Gogolen, and George Gundry at a central point and hopped in their car for most of the trip.  Had to ride the hump the whole way.  The guys swore &quot;the hump brought me luck.  Humps are lucky.&quot;<br />
<br />
Got there an hour early.  Got mashed potatoes at KFC for breakfast/lunch.  Turnout was 50 people.  Was playing this 80-card Nazgul oddity that I&#39;ve been playing (with slight modifications) since November.  E-mail or d-mail me if you want a decklist, it&#39;s too unconventionally big to post and not get slammed for size.  Onto the games, it was a REALLY long day so I don&#39;t remember all the details on every single one, especially the early ones.  I also don&#39;t remember that much about anyone&#39;s fellowship, since I was usually ahead and didn&#39;t need to worry about killing them. <br />
<br />
Game 1 vs. John Rowe (Sauron)<br />
<br />
First thing he does when I sit down is ask me if I&#39;ve ever played in a tournament before.  I go first.  He gets out an early Orc Bowmen first turn (grr) and when I double move he gets out an Under the Watching Eye.  Since I never found my Secret Sentinels the entire game, they stayed there, plus the second Orc Bowmen he got out on my second turn.  I didn&#39;t see any Enduring Evils the whole game, which was my main concern, and I also got Galadriel and her Mirror working early.  Ungodly luck, I suppose, but I kept yanking out his Tower Assassins and Morgul Hunters -- most of the damage I was taking was from the conditions, and he also had some You Bring Great Evil action going on too.  I don&#39;t remember much about his fellowship, but I had him slowed down a lot -- he was at 6 when I hit 9.  He brought out a bunch of minions at 9, but I had 2 PATHS to keep FRodo alive.  Full win (3)<br />
<br />
Game 2 vs. ? (Nazgul)<br />
<br />
I SO thought I had this game lost by site 3... I went first, and since we were both playing Nazgul we held each other to single moves at 2.  He had only brought out 1, but he killed my Sam and put a wound on Arwen.  I brought out 2, but he had more characters out than I did so he weathered it about the same.  I move to 3 (the ford), and he brings out 2 (Enquea and a 12, I forget which one) and a blade tip -- great, 1 I could have handled.  I&#39;m faced with the decision of gunning one twice and letting Frodo PATHS him (and the other putting 1 on Legolas and Arwen) or having Arwen die and Legolas taking 2 and a blade tip.  BUT, I play All Blades Perish, and I&#39;ve killed too many Frodos relying on a PATHS to risk falling prey to my own trick.  I opt for choice #2.  Imagine my relief when I saw him play ABP later...  So I land in Rivendell with Frodo and a blade tipped Legolas.  I thought I was doomed.  However, on my next turn... Aragorn and Boromir with toys show up!  Hallelujah!  I single moved to 4, jumped from 4 to 6 with an ARV, Thror&#39;s Map, and a Celeborn to sacrifice if need be (ensuring Legolas&#39; survival past site 6, cuz those Secret Sentinels failed to show up AGAIN...)  He was held to single moves for the rest of the game.  I lost Legolas at site 7 (since he was going to die anyway) and Aragorn and Boromir carried Frodo to victory.<br />
Full win (6)<br />
<br />
Game 3 vs. Jesse Carlucci (Uruk-Hai)<br />
<br />
I had played Jesse before at the last tournament I ran, so I figured he would still be running Uruks.  I was right.  He actually bid higher than I did and did NOT start the Green Dragon, so I had to switch up and run with Arwen and Sam as my starting fellowship.  Good thing too, since he had a couple of random Enqueas thrown in the mix just in case.  We both stopped each other at 2 (and I had NOTHING in my hand to bring down at 3), and he was stopped at 3 next turn.  Me, figuring this is states, he went first, and it&#39;s balls to the wall time, decide to move through Rivendell to double move 2-4.  Of course, I had a Gondor&#39;s Vengeance to help, but still... So he ends up going 1-2, 2-3, 3-5, and 5-7.  I went 1-2, 2-4, 4-6, and 6-7.  But since he had gone first, he still had the advantage.  He moves to 8.  Decisions, decisions... I had 4 Nazgul in my hand.  Enough to overwhelm, I THINK... if only I had enough twilight.  So after some quick calculations, I figure out that if he double moves and I spend nothing this shadow phase, I should be gold.  So I plaster an evil smile on my phase and announce that I&#39;m passing.  So he looks at me, counts the twilight a few times, looks at me again, and decides to Sting as a regroup action.  He sees 4 Nazgul that he KNOWS I can bring down, plus whatever I draw... not being a fool, he stops, since I&#39;m pretty beat up as it is and I&#39;d have to double move to win, even with the 3 PATHS he knows I have in my hand it&#39;s a stretch.  Do I manage it?  Of course!  Granted, all I have left when the smoke clears is a Frodo with 4 wounds and 5 burdens, but the important thing is that I had Frodo left.  I lost at least one character at site 8, but with 3 PATHS all I had to worry about at 9 were troops, which he had already burnt.<br />
Full win (9)<br />
<br />
Game 4 vs. Tim McGarvey (Moria)<br />
I went first this game, thank God.  I hadn&#39;t lost to a Moria deck in months, so I figured I had it made... I ended up winning this one on a wish and a prayer.  I was ahead the whole game, so I wasn&#39;t worried about him outracing me (much) but he got his mirror out before I did... and started yanking the PATHS I was accruing for site 9 (which is how I play, setting up the perfect hand).  I couldn&#39;t find ANY of my anti-mirror stuff.  He ended up getting 2 all told.  By the time I was moving into site 6, I was DESPERATE for fellowship stuff to keep me alive since I had lost a couple of companions at the bridge.  So I was ditching my shadow like crazy, which he knew.  I did my move into 6 when he was at 5, and he opted to stop at 6 instead of double moving into 7, since I pretty much had nothing in my hand.  Piece of luck #1.  So I move to 7, stop... then I have to double move to 9 in order to win, since I know I won&#39;t be able to overwhelm him at this point.  I lose Boromir at site 8, but I do Secret Sentinels to get rid of his TAC.  This leaves me with an exhausted Aragorn, Frodo, and 1 PATHS against whatever he can bring down at 9 with the 2 orcs left over from 8 (the ones that double-teamed Boromir), and he has at least 1 armory out.  He regroups his hand, draws a couple extra cards for my burdens at the summit, and draws... a balrog.  The 2 orcs get mopped up and I win.<br />
Full win (12)<br />
<br />
Game 5 vs. Shawn Drew (twilight denial/ Moria)<br />
I go first.  I get 7 shadow cards in my opening hand.  Crappiest opening hand EVER.  But since I didn&#39;t know at the time he was playing denial, I double move to 3 with no problems.  I still managed to drop a lot of shadow cards since I had blade tips and black breaths and gates and stuff, but I still couldn&#39;t find a gosh darnit thing that I needed.  At the bridge he managed to turn 13 pool into a Cave Troll, a Balrog, 3 orcs, and 2 scimitars.  Vs. Frodo, Arwen, Legolas, and Sam.  (Aragorn, Boromir, and their lovely, lovely armor never showed up).  Well, I have 3 PATHS, so Frodo takes out the Cave Troll, but everyone else dies on the first round of combat so Frodo is left to tackle the fierce Balrog.  The game was over in about 5 minutes.  And what are the next 4 cards in my deck?  Gwemegil, Boromir, a Nazgul, and armor.  A better draw would have helped, but it was a well-designed deck.  Grrr...<br />
Full Loss (13)<br />
<br />
Game 6 vs. Matthew Nixon, i think (Twilight Denial/ Moria)<br />
So this guy sits down and tells me that I just played a friend of his and they have the same deck, card for card.  Lovely?  I do get Aragorn in my opening hand, though, which would have helped last game:)  It was pretty much a repeat of the last game, except I had Aragorn with a flaming brand and armor at the bridge and there was no troll, just a bunch more orcs.  I was able to save my PATHS until the end, knocked out a bunch of his shadow cards with the Mirror, and killed a TAC, a Relics, and 2 Armories with Secret Sentinels.  I was able to single move since I got the jump with a 1-3 move and I was beating him up pretty badly.  PATHS took care of the rest.<br />
Full Win (16)<br />
<br />
Game 7 vs. ? (Uruk-Hai)<br />
I don&#39;t remember this game AT ALL, except I used the mirror at site 7 to yank some key minions, I used Gondor&#39;s Vengeance at site 8 to get rid of a troop (which won me the game, since at 9 he brought down 2 more troops and I only had 3 PATHS), and he had really cool poker chips as tokens.<br />
Full Win (19)<br />
<br />
Game 8 vs. Alouk something (spelled wrong) (Moria archery)<br />
His name got completely butchered, but he was 7-0 going into this game with 2 timed wins.  I went first and stayed ahead of him the whole game.  I got Thror&#39;s Map out, so I didn&#39;t have to deal with the Brown Lands or anything, which was nice.  He had a TON of archery, though, and I was getting hit like crazy.  I think he only double-moved once, so I had some breathing room, but it was still very, very ugly.  The upshot is I move to site 9 and he pulls out 5 archery on me.  Arwen takes 1 and dies, Boromir takes 1 and dies, and Frodo takes SIX burdens, leaving him with a total of 7.  And Frodo is all I have left, and he&#39;s exhausted to boot.  So I got corrupted.  I&#39;m facing a Moria Archer Troop with a Moria Axe, and a bunch of vitality 1 archers.  I PATHS, he sacks his only armory to save one of the scrubs.  I PATHS again, which kills off the saved scrub, but the power 10 damage +1 archer troop beats my 4 wounds, 9 burdens Frodo.  I already have the ring on, I can&#39;t even take it off to choose to DIE instead of being corrupted.<br />
<br />
This round, the top 3 were my undefeated opponent, me (at 6-1), and Shawn, the other guy who beat me (also at 6-1).  I thought I was sunk, but it turns out Shawn lost his game too, to Tim McGarvey.  There are 5 6-2&#39;s -- but I actually got to SEE the benefit of playing at the top tables all day.  My opposition total was 145, since the worst finish one of my opponents had was 4-4.  Made the final, baby.  And I have to play the guy that just beat me.<br />
<br />
Finals vs. the guy I just played, don&#39;t want to butcher his name again.<br />
<br />
I went first again, and all I can say is I got better card flow this time.  I got the Secret Sentinels when I needed them, I had all my allies out at 6 to soak up archery (which I didn&#39;t last time) so my companions were cleaner pulling out of 6, and he wasn&#39;t able to do any double moves, which meant I could afford to stop more and have Aragorn take off more wounds.  I did make some mistakes (which my carpool was all too happy to point out to me on the way home), but when I hit 9 I only had 1 wound on Aragorn and 1 on Boromir.  I still took 5 archery, but the 2 of them survived and FRodo only took 4 burdens.  I also had the double PATHS once again and he did have an armory, but the 1 he was able to save against Frodo wasn&#39;t enough to overwhelm and I used the 2nd PATHS anyway, cuz I could:)  <br />
<br />
So I won a nifty binder that I can use as a subtle way to let people know &quot;hey!  I don&#39;t suck at this!&quot; and a bunch of packs and foils, as well as the precious, precious day 2 bye... now day 1 = bar:)  I was all smiley on the way home (which irritated everybody, especially Dalton:).  So I get home around 12:30 to the raging party going on at my house that I had THOUGHT I&#39;d be home around 10 for, was too exhausted to take part, and went to sleep after shoving a pillow over my head.<br />
<br />
Props:<br />
Mike and Jim, GREAT tournament.<br />
<br />
Everybody who came -- 50 players?  Fantastic turnout!<br />
<br />
All of my opponents -- if you guys hadn&#39;t been so good, I wouldn&#39;t have made the final.  Almost makes the elevated blood pressure, ulcers, and massive headache worth it (I didn&#39;t have an easy game all day).<br />
<br />
Slops:<br />
Getting up early and being too beat to party.  I&#39;m getting old! <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3676&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
